  "body": "### Overview\r\n`helm install` command slips into a perpetual loop if `install` routine fails (for any reason).\r\n\r\n### Change:\r\nRemove retry loop from `helm_helper.go` install routine.\r\n\r\nRationale: If/when `install` fails there is a very high probability that all subsequent install attempts will fail as well. So far I have encountered a couple of times when `helm install` would fail, both dealing with invalid install configurations (wrong RBAC, duplicated resource, etc), i.e. nonrecoverable failures.\r\n\r\nWhich issue is resolved by this Pull Request:\r\nResolves #1620 \r\n\r\nChecklist:\r\n- [ ] Documentation has been updated, if necessary.\r\n- [ ] Pending release notes updated with breaking and/or notable changes, if necessary.\r\n",
